article.headline: VMI 80, Presbyterian 74
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Austin Kenon scored 13 points and hit a 3-pointer to spark Virginia Military Institute's decisive 6-0 run late in an 80-74 win over Presbyterian on Thursday night. Kenon was one of five Keydets (16-12, 9-8 Big South Conference) to score in double figures as Nick Gore added 13 and Michael Sparks 12. D.J. Covington and Ron Burks chipped in 10 each for VMI, which won for the first time in Clinton, S.C. Tied at 56 with 10:21 to go, the Keydets scored seven straight to go up 63-56 with 8:33 remaining. The Blue Hose (12-18, 6-11) then answered with a 9-2 run to tie it back up, 65-65 with 4:30 left. Both teams traded baskets and with 1:13 to go, it was tied for the ninth time, before scoring six straight for the final margin. The Keydets scored 29 points off 20 turnovers. Presbyterian was led by Walt Allen's career-highs of 19 points and 15 rebounds.
